derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 16th cent.: from late Latin indisputabilis, from in- 'not' + disputabilis (see disputable)

entry.tran: 无可争辩的;不容置疑的
entry.def: If you say that something is indisputable, you are emphasizing that it is true and cannot be shown to be untrue.
